717598f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 61st Street
717598f-a.text:
Broadway, west side, north from 6lst Street. Boulevard, as the
present Broadway, north of Columbus Circle was then called, was a
favorite street for cyclists, as this picture shows. The Empire
Hotel is seen in the centre, on the S.W. corner of 63rd Street.
This will later be rebuilt as a 14-story hotel.
About 1895.
International News.
